title: 820-3436 no power
message:
macbook pro 820-3436 no power, green light no fan spin
visual inspection, dirty, ssd getting warm
rails
ppbus 12.58 pp5vs5 5v pp3v3s5 3.3
pp3v3s4 0.45v 3v3 sus 1.94 3v3s3 0
pp3v3 s4 fet 0.334 pp5vs4 reg 0 P5VS4RS3_EN 0
PM_SLP_S4_L 0 (no i did not rehot cpu bro)
replaced u1950, cpu warm still no sys pwrok

title: 820-3436 no power
message: If CPU and SSD are getting warm then some rails must be powering on. Check voltages on CPU Vcore and other coils.

title: 820-3436 no power
message: PPVCC_S0_CPU is 0 obviously,    pp3v3 s0. 1.9v 3v3 sus 3.3         3v3s4  0.444     other coils?  the point is im missing pm_slp_s4_L, without this the cpu wont power on

title: 820-3436 no power
message: How is the CPU getting warm then? Some rail to the CPU must be powering it, same goes for the SSD.

title: 820-3436 no power
message:
it would be nice if i had some hints, PP3V3_S0SW_SSD  3.3v  SSD_RESET_CONN_L  0        ssd_pwr_en 1.725   ssd_clkreq_l  2.781
PP1V05_S0_CPU_VCCST  0        CPU_VCCST_PWRGD   0,  cpu is no longer getting warm, so can we go back to the original issue

title: 820-3436 no power
message:
PP3V3_S0SW_SSD should not be high. SSD_PWR_EN at 1.7V is very strange as this is pulled up from 3V_S0.  ssd_clkreq_l at 2.7V is also weird, signal is also pulled up from 3V_S0. What is the voltage on PP3V3_S0?

Some history on this board may also help as I truly have no idea what is going on here.
